  "title": "SEO & SEM Specialist",
  "description": "<h3><strong>Join Our Team as a SEO & SEM Specialist at Skills Development Academy!</strong></h3><p>Are you passionate about digital marketing and ready to make an impact? Skills Development Academy is expanding, and we're looking for skilled SEO & SEM Specialists to join our dynamic team. As a SEO & SEM Specialist with us, you will play a crucial role in driving our digital marketing campaigns to new heights.</p><p><strong>Position Overview:</strong> </p><p>We are seeking a skilled and experienced SEO & SEM Specialist to join our dynamic marketing team. The ideal candidate will have a proven track record of managing effective Google Ads campaigns with a focus on maximizing ROI and driving conversions. You will be responsible for overseeing our Google advertising strategy, from conception to execution and analysis.</p><p><strong>Key Responsibilities:</strong><br />• Develop, implement, and manage Google Ads campaigns, including search, display, and video ads<br />• Conduct keyword research and selection for pay-per-click (PPC) campaigns and SEO initiatives<br />• Analyze campaign performance and adjust strategies to maximize return on ad spend (ROAS)<br />• Manage a substantial advertising budget effectively, ensuring maximum ROI.<br />• Monitor and report on campaign results, providing actionable insights and recommendations<br />• Stay up-to-date with the latest Google Ads features and best practices<br />• Collaborate with other marketing team members to align Google Ads strategies with overall marketing goals<br />• Ensure all Google advertising initiatives align with brand messaging and company objectives</p><p><strong>Qualifications:</strong><br />• Proven work experience as a Google Ads Specialist or similar role<br />• Solid understanding and experience with Google Ads (including search, display, and YouTube)<br />• Experience managing $30,000 - $50,000 advertising budget with a focus on delivering 4-5x ROAS<br />• Strong analytical skills and experience with Google Analytics and other relevant tools<br />• Ability to translate complex data into actionable campaign improvements<br />• Strong attention to detail and ability to work under tight deadlines<br />• Strong verbal and written communication skills<br />• Bachelor's degree in Marketing or relevant field<br />• At least 2 years of professional working experience in Google Ads or PPC advertising</p>",
